Turns out, the two individuals were Astronomer CEO Andy Byron â€” who has since resigned â€” and his companyâ€™s then-HR executive, Kristin Cabot, both of whom were married to other people at the time. In a New York Times piece published many months after the fact, Cabot explained that she had already been separated from her husband by then, and that nothing physical had gone on between herself and her boss before the concert.

â€œI made a bad decision and had a couple of High Noons and danced and acted inappropriately with my boss,â€ she told the publication. â€œAnd itâ€™s not nothing. And I took accountability and I gave up my career for that.â€

